				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Why Amazon Must Be Stopped</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-10-13T17:12:18+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">October 13, 2014 1:12 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">October 13, 2014 1:12 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/13/today-in-small-business-why-amazon-must-be-stopped/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Why Amazon Must Be Stopped" data-description="Revolution is sexy. A contrarian developer is looking to buy properties in Atlantic City. A pioneer of hair products for black people dies at 82.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A Goldman Sachs economist <a href="//www.calculatedriskblog.com/2014/10/goldman-on-2015-potential-renewed.html?">predicts</a> that 2015 will bring &#8220;potential renewed uncertainty around fiscal deadlines.&#8221;</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retailing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The editor of The New Republic <a href="//www.newrepublic.com/article/119769/amazons-monopoly-must-be-broken-radical-plan-tech-giant?">lays out a case</a> for why Amazon âmust be stopped.â</li>
<li>Crumbs <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/238415">is coming back</a> (but you may not recognize it).</li>
<li>Here is how McDonald&#8217;s could serve &#8220;<a href="//civileats.com/2014/10/13/how-mcdonalds-could-serve-up-a-happier-meal/">a happier meal.</a>&#8221;</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-89288"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A contrarian developer is <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/blog/real-estate/2014/10/blatstein-to-buy-pier-shops-in-atlantic-city.html">looking to buy properties in Atlantic City</a>.</li>
<li>Here is how <a href="//finance.yahoo.com/news/13-old-ceo-made-deal-152407213.html">a 13-year-old made a deal</a> with a âShark Tankâ investor without his fatherâs help.</li>
<li>And here is how two parents <a href="//www.blogtrepreneur.com/2014/10/12/two-parents-turn-700-savings-million-dollar-business/">turned $700 in savings</a> into a million-dollar business.</li>
<li>A professional protester has started a company called <a title="Company website" href="//www.revolutionissexy.com/">Revolution Is Sexy</a>, which she hopes to develop into a one-stop shopping outlet for effective demonstrating.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A contest in Nelsonville, Ohio, is <a href="//www.athensohiotoday.com/news/start-it-up-nelsonville-contest-to-award-to-local-entrepreneurs/article_336973ef-6ed1-593c-8027-5b346c0e267b.html">offering a $10,000 grand prize</a> to local businesses and interested entrepreneurs who develop the best new business plan.</li>
<li>In Texas, a family-owned vinyl record store <a href="//herald-zeitung.com/business/article_d8b25b4e-51d9-11e4-980e-678c7a8d126b.html">is succeeding</a>.</li>
<li>Women are <a href="//m.cjonline.com/news/business/2014-10-11/women-approach-parity-men-owning-businesses-kansas#gsc.tab=0">approaching parity</a> with men on owning businesses in Kansas, according to a report.</li>
<li>A zombie <a href="//minnesota.cbslocal.com/2014/10/11/zombie-pub-crawl-eating-into-some-retailers-bottom-line/">pub crawl</a> is eating into someÂ retail sales in Minneapolis.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The European Union is expected to unveil a <a href="//www.theguardian.com/world/2014/oct/12/eu-business-deregulation-concern-worker-rights">deregulation plan</a> this week that will exempt small businesses from business regulations.</li>
<li>Some Italian businesses are being forced into a <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/kenrapoza/2014/10/11/for-some-italian-businesses-an-uneasy-and-growing-dependence-on-foreigners/">growing dependence</a> on foreign customers.</li>
<li>Should the United States <a href="//www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2014/10/12/should-the-us-normalize-relations-with-cuba">normalize relations with Cuba</a>?</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A drug-testing service reports that, for <a href="//triblive.com/business/headlines/6809069-74/drug-marijuana-quest#axzz3Fwoxuwo0">the first time</a> in more than a decade, more applicants and workers are testing positive for drug use than in the year before.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Why <a href="//www.smallbusinessheroes.co.uk/features/renewable-energy-makes-financial-sense/#ixzz3FxlZqGoz">investing in renewable energy</a> makes financial sense for your business.</li>
<li>Why sales superstars <a href="//theresourcefulceo.com/2014/10/why-sales-superstars-may-not-become-sales-management-superstars/">may not become</a> sales management superstars.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Since 2010, <a href="https://gigaom.com/2014/10/08/patent-trolling-pays-since-2010-trolls-have-made-3-times-as-much-money-in-court-as-real-companies/">patent trolls</a> have made three times as much money in court as real companies.</li>
<li>A harassed game developer is <a href="//www.theverge.com/2014/10/11/6962823/harassed-game-developer-driven-from-home-after-death-threats">driven from her home</a> after receiving death threats on Twitter.</li>
<li>Google is <a href="//venturebeat.com/2014/10/12/the-doctor-will-see-you-now-through-google/">testing a new feature</a> to allow users to speak to doctors online.</li>
<li>In what is being called the âSnappening,â a <a href="//www.newsweek.com/snappening-hack-may-leak-200000-sensitive-snapchat-photos-276896">hack of the photo-sharing service Snapchat</a> may expose hundreds of thousands of personal photos.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here is some advice on getting your Dun &amp; Bradstreet report <a href="//fitsmallbusiness.com/db-credit-report/">into shape</a>.</li>
<li>Here is what small businesses <a href="//blog.fundinggates.com/2014/10/small-businesses-need-know-p2p-lending/">need to know</a> about peer-to-peer lending.</li>
<li>Venture capitalists are investing inÂ <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/13/business/venture-capitalists-return-to-backing-science-start-ups.html">science-based start-ups</a> again.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Another <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/apples-oct-16-event-heres-what-we-expect/#ftag=CAD590a51e">big Apple event</a> is coming this week.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Obituary</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/11/business/comer-cottrell-pioneer-of-hair-products-for-blacks-dies-at-82.html">pioneer of hair products</a> for black people dies at 82.</li>
</ul>
